/i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Ithel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name derived from the Greek, signifying 'blooming luxuriantly, flourishing, rich.'. It is from Ithel that we have first the name Ap-Ithel, then by corruption, Bithell and Bethell."],"variants":[{"name":"Bithell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]},{"name":"Bethell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]}]},{"name":"Felyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Guadalupe, Ignacio, Jose, Marcos, Ruben, Agustin, Alfredo, Alvino, Amalio, Ana, Apolonio, Carlos.","Irish: variant of   Phelan  .","Hispanic (<b>Felán</b>): unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Phelan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Kieran, Aine, Declan, Finbarr.","Irish:","Anglicized form of <b>Ó Faoláin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Faolán</i>’, see   Whelan  ."]}]},{"name":"Gronwy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name of uncertain derivation, borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by  Goronwy the Staunch , Lord of Penllyn. He became the lover of the flower-maiden Blodeuedd and murdered her husband  Lleu Llaw Gyffes , but Lleu was later restored to life and definitively dispatched Goronwy."],"variants":[{"name":"Gronw","meanings":["Variant of   Goronwy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gronwy ap Hwfa ap Ithel Felyn of Powys was born about 1130, in Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Hwfa ap Ithel Felyn ap Llewelyn Fychan, was 36 and his mother, Yslani, was 27. He had at least 2 sons with unknown."},"et":{"circa 1130–":"umbes 1130–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1146–Male":"1146–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1095–1176":"1095–1176","1104–1171":"1104–1171","1104":"1104","circa 1130":"umbes 1130","1146":"1146","circa 1160":"umbes 1160","1